00:40:15.820 --> 00:40:19.410
too far from each other,
to recognize that together.

00:40:19.410 --> 00:40:23.030
And in this book here,
I talk about pleasure

00:40:23.030 --> 00:40:25.630
and what was the name of
that lord, by the way?

00:40:25.630 --> 00:40:29.040
I'm not trying to laugh at
him, I'm feeling sad for him.

00:40:29.040 --> 00:40:30.600
What?

00:40:30.600 --> 00:40:31.370
Sewell.

00:40:31.370 --> 00:40:33.860
I mean, he was trying
to find pleasure.

00:40:33.860 --> 00:40:36.030
I mean, of course what he
was trying to do, I guess,

00:40:36.030 --> 00:40:39.970
was to find something
that would make him,

00:40:39.970 --> 00:40:42.330
deep down-- the
craving for happiness

00:40:42.330 --> 00:40:43.410
is there in all of us.

00:40:43.410 --> 00:40:45.440
And he looked for it
in the wrong place.

00:40:45.440 --> 00:40:49.090
And it's very sad and I
certainly don't laugh at him.

00:40:49.090 --> 00:40:52.440
But I talk about going through
pleasure into happiness.

00:40:52.440 --> 00:40:55.600
And I talk about how we
could move towards happiness

00:40:55.600 --> 00:40:58.660
by learning to, A.
accept ourselves,

00:40:58.660 --> 00:41:01.130
B, belonging is
really important,

00:41:01.130 --> 00:41:04.510
C, character, which is all
about playing to our character

00:41:04.510 --> 00:41:08.610
strengths and not
being-- playing

00:41:08.610 --> 00:41:12.280
from our great qualities and
not worrying too much about we

00:41:12.280 --> 00:41:13.440
can't do.

00:41:13.440 --> 00:41:15.370
About having a
discipline, which is

00:41:15.370 --> 00:41:18.350
what I was saying there about--
otherwise it will just simply--

00:41:18.350 --> 00:41:20.670
your life will suddenly go.

00:41:20.670 --> 00:41:24.290
Empathy, really truly
emphasizing with each other

00:41:24.290 --> 00:41:26.060
and with ourselves.

00:41:26.060 --> 00:41:28.750
Having a focus in life.

00:41:28.750 --> 00:41:30.480
Giving.

00:41:30.480 --> 00:41:34.840
Undoubtedly those people who, if
you want to feel good, do good.

00:41:34.840 --> 00:41:35.820
Do good to others.

00:41:35.820 --> 00:41:37.620
It always makes us feel better.

00:41:37.620 --> 00:41:40.290
Those of you volunteer will
know exactly what I mean.

00:41:40.290 --> 00:41:43.850
And H is to health, and
taking our physical,

00:41:43.850 --> 00:41:45.810
mental, and psychological
health seriously

00:41:45.810 --> 00:41:47.560
is fundamental in happiness.

00:41:47.560 --> 00:41:50.630
A happy mind does
equal-- and a happy body

00:41:50.630 --> 00:41:52.240
will mean a happy mind.

00:41:52.240 --> 00:41:55.630
If you jog and run
and you all know that.

00:41:55.630 --> 00:41:59.280
And if you eat well, conversely
if you do the wrong things,

00:41:59.280 --> 00:42:00.210
you won't feel happy.

00:42:00.210 --> 00:42:04.650
And then five ways to get
beyond happiness, inquiry, being

00:42:04.650 --> 00:42:08.680
on a journey, karma,
which is about thinking

00:42:08.680 --> 00:42:10.660
about the hurt
you've done to others

00:42:10.660 --> 00:42:16.120
and trying to seek
forgiveness, to forgive others

00:42:16.120 --> 00:42:17.740
and on it goes.

00:42:17.740 --> 00:42:18.740
So that's the book.

00:42:18.740 --> 00:42:20.698
I don't know if there
are any questions in just

00:42:20.698 --> 00:42:22.010
the remaining time.

00:42:22.010 --> 00:42:24.810
It's a topic I absolutely love.

00:42:24.810 --> 00:42:28.500
And it came out of my own
experience and to some extent

00:42:28.500 --> 00:42:34.040
my family's experience
of being not very happy,

00:42:34.040 --> 00:42:35.330
certainly my experience.

00:42:35.330 --> 00:42:39.020
I was pretty profoundly
unhappy when I was younger.

00:42:42.630 --> 00:42:44.220
So and it was near here.

00:42:44.220 --> 00:42:47.060
It was about two
blocks south of here

00:42:47.060 --> 00:42:50.280
that one day when I was
writing my doctoral thesis.

00:42:50.280 --> 00:42:54.750
When I was at LSE, I used to
work at the British Museum.

00:42:54.750 --> 00:43:00.800
And I went past this
secondhand bookshop

00:43:00.800 --> 00:43:04.810
and there was this book that
said, do you want to be happy?

00:43:04.810 --> 00:43:07.179
And I was kind of interested,
but didn't go and buy it.

00:43:07.179 --> 00:43:08.720
The next day I
thought I would buy it

00:43:08.720 --> 00:43:09.880
and it wasn't in the shop.

00:43:09.880 --> 00:43:11.379
Because it was a
secondhand bookshop

00:43:11.379 --> 00:43:14.675
they've got no idea who wrote
the book or what it was.

00:43:14.675 --> 00:43:17.950
So as I say in the book,
I've written the kind of book

00:43:17.950 --> 00:43:20.120
I would have wanted
that to be, so I could

00:43:20.120 --> 00:43:22.710
have read that when I was 25.

00:43:22.710 --> 00:43:25.620
OK any questions on anything?

